The international community called for justice in Lebanon after the assassination of former Prime Minister Rafik Hariri.
Blame was placed on the Lebanese and Syrian authorities, sparking demands for an international investigation.
Amidst mourning and protests, suspicions arose regarding Syria's involvement.
Hariri's funeral drew massive crowds, with calls for Syrian withdrawal from Lebanon intensifying.
The tragic event marked a turning point in Lebanese-Syrian relations.
Despite initial uncertainty, the investigation continued, shedding light on the complex political landscape surrounding Hariri's untimely death.
The legacy of a man dedicated to peace and progress was forever altered by this senseless act of violence.
